        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} was previously healthy with no chronic medical conditions documented. His parent reports a recent cold-like illness before the onset of cough, consistent with the common viral trigger for acute bronchitis [MEDLINEPLUS:J20.9]. He attends preschool and has frequent exposure to other children with respiratory infections, which increases the chance of viral spread through coughing and contact [MEDLINEPLUS:J20.9].\n\nThere is no history suggesting chronic bronchitis or other long-standing lung disease. He has had occasional recurrent upper respiratory tract infections in the past, as can be associated with acute bronchitis presentations [SNOMED:J20.9]. No prior hospitalizations are reported. The family is advised to avoid tobacco smoke exposure because exposure to tobacco smoke, air pollution, dusts, vapors, and fumes can contribute to bronchitis [MEDLINEPLUS:J20.9]."
          }
        ]
      }
